ign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Beastlord Pet Info~</span><hr size=1> There has been a lot of confusion about the location of BL spells. I've been playing almost since the servers came up and I'd like to share what I've found out to save other BL's some time.<br><br>Can't find your pet spell at level 9? There isn't one! At level 9 under your 'abilities' there will be a new skill, 'Summon Warder'. This is not a trainable skill and it appears automagically.<br><br>The pet doesn't require mana (!) and has about about 8-12 sec cast time.  Assuming you aren't too far ahead of the pet when you zone, he usually zones with you.<br><br>There are 3 lines a BL spells (not the shaman shared ones).<br><br>- Pet Level Buff<br>- Pet Heal Line<br>- Imbue Pet with DD/taunt proc<br><br>The level buff and heal lines are only on the moon (AFAIK). The Imbue DD line should be available on a new NPC in each town where BLs can start.<br><br>The pet at 9 was hitting for 8, and with the pet level buff he was hitting for 10. When you cast the level buff on your pet, you see..<br><br>Sukar's Warder says, 'Ding!'<br><br>which is funny to see. It also looked like my pet got a little bigger too. Iksar BL pets are TINY. They nerfed the size of the scaled wolf pups and the warders are very hard to find sometimes.<br><br>At 15 the pet was hitting for 12 unbuffed. I was unable get a copy of the level 15 pet level buff (just the 9 and 22 versions [on the moon]).<br><br>At lev 15 I made a pet, buffed him with the lighting DD proc (no level buff).. he was light blue to me and taking blues down no problem solo. I've seen the DD proc up to 3 times a fight and seems to help a great deal.<br><br>Unbuffed my pet at level 15 (again, light blue con without level buff) has about 240-270hp. I'm not sure how this compares to mage/necro pets.<br><br>It's definately too early to tell how the class will pan out in the long haul but it's been a blast so far.<br><br>Hope this info will save you BLs some time...<br><br>If anyone knows where to find the level 15 pet level buff, please post where!<br><br>~Sukar, IKS BL <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvyperhandgrimslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vyperhand Grimslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, I don't use roids thx</span><br>  Posts: 1101<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/01 3:14:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.conan.no/mig/albums/Diverse/Conan_desktops/Ovi_Hondru_01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beastlord Pet Info~</span><hr size=1> The lvl 15 ding buff is in the town near the nexus. i believe i saw your corpse there its close to where you died.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiberar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iberar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Megalomaniac</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/01 6:40:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beastlord Pet Info~</span><hr size=1>   Sigh, this is gonna make the ultimate solo pet.<br><br>Iberar Megalomaniac<br>56th Season Arch-Magus<br>Colleague of Sanctuary<br>Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usheanearrowless.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheane Arrowless</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br